<TITLE> Mohammedan rout Mariner Youngs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com) - Mohammedan Sporting Club came from behind to thrash Dhaka Mariner Youngs Club 3-1 in the Premier Division Hockey League at Moulana Bhasani National Hockey Stadium Thursday. Wari Club tasted the first triumph in six matches when they handed a 2-0 defeat to Shadharan Bima in the day's second match. Mohammedan raised their point tally to 16 from six outings, two points behind leaders Abahani Limited, who earned maximum 18 points from six matches. Ranjan Banik gave Mariner Youngs a lead in the 12th minute while Pakistani recruit M Sabbir restored the margin for Mohammedan through a field goal just one minute before the lemon break. After the breather, defender Musa Mia converted a penalty corner to double the lead for Mohammedan, who saw Golam Mostafa score team's third goal to ensure their fifth win in five matches. In the other match of the day, Wari took a 30-minute lead against Bima with the help of Faisal while Tapu ensured Wari's first triumph scoring in the 47th minute. 
